After three years of riding, there was a shift in perspectives for both the benefits and limitations of e‐bikes (see Table 3 ). In particular, over time, participants increasingly felt that e‐bikes were beneficial for replacing car trips and made commuting more enjoyable overall.
Table 3. Most frequently cited benefits and limitations over time
	Round 1 	Round 2
